    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Uppermost cornices of masonry or other noncombustible material atop chimneys, either as an ornament or as a cover; for extra components specifically intended to cover flue openings, use "chimney hoods."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
